<h3>Maven</h3>
<p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;">&#160;</p>
<p>What you might not notice in this demo is that it is using m2e/wtp and the JBoss Tools specific m2e configurators behind the scenes to</p>
<p>automatically have the related plugins for the project automatically configured based on the Maven metadata instead of you having to manually configure and setup the tools.</p>
<p style="min-height: 8pt; height: 8pt; padding: 0px;">&#160;</p>
<p>In upcoming releases of JBoss Tools you will see even tighter integration with Seam Forge and with Maven to make you even more productive in working with JEE 6 based technologies. </p>
